From b45b0dd6e1b92de36c48df55825e7b9b17d0c509 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Arecsu <alejandro9r@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 4 May 2026 22:15:24 -0300
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] winewayland: floor client subsurface position to hide
 fractional-scale edge gaps

A Vulkan client subsurface (the canvas in apps such as Affinity Designer
or Photo) is positioned within its parent toplevel using
wl_subsurface_set_position, which takes integer logical coordinates.
At fractional scale (e.g. 1.5x), the buffer-pixel offset of the client
area against the parent rarely converts to an integer logical position,
and round-to-nearest can place the subsurface a sub-pixel later than
the boundary up to which the parent's GDI surface has cleared the
canvas-area background. The compositor's resampler then exposes that
sub-pixel of cleared background as a thin lighter line on the top and
left edges of the canvas. The same artifact appears in detached canvas
mode because the underlying mechanism (logical-pixel rounding of a
buffer-pixel offset) is identical there.

Floor the position so the subsurface always starts at or before the
boundary, and ceil the size so it still extends to the original right
and bottom edges. The subsurface ends up at most one buffer pixel
larger than the source widget rect; the extra pixel is hidden behind
the parent's GDI panel (or off the screen edge for a detached canvas)
and the lighter line disappears.
---
 dlls/winewayland.drv/wayland_surface.c | 15 ++++++++++++---
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/dlls/winewayland.drv/wayland_surface.c b/dlls/winewayland.drv/wayland_surface.c
index f9842e98fb91..e134339800e1 100644
--- a/dlls/winewayland.drv/wayland_surface.c
+++ b/dlls/winewayland.drv/wayland_surface.c
@@ -865,9 +865,18 @@ static void wayland_surface_reconfigure_client(struct wayland_surface *surface,
     client_width = client_rect->right - client_rect->left;
     client_height = client_rect->bottom - client_rect->top;
 
-    wayland_surface_coords_from_window(surface, client_x, client_y, &x, &y);
-    wayland_surface_coords_from_window(surface, client_width, client_height,
-                                       &width, &height);
+    /* Floor-round the client subsurface position rather than round-to-nearest:
+     * the parent's GDI surface has cleared the area underneath this client up
+     * to buffer pixel client_{x,y}, but at fractional scale a round-to-nearest
+     * subsurface position can land a sub-pixel later than that boundary,
+     * exposing a thin strip of the parent's clear color (typically white) at
+     * the top and left edges. Flooring guarantees the subsurface starts at or
+     * before the boundary, hiding the strip. Use ceil for the size so the
+     * subsurface still extends to the original right/bottom edge. */
+    x = (int)floor((double)client_x / surface->window.scale);
+    y = (int)floor((double)client_y / surface->window.scale);
+    width  = (int)ceil ((double)(client_x + client_width)  / surface->window.scale) - x;
+    height = (int)ceil ((double)(client_y + client_height) / surface->window.scale) - y;
 
     TRACE("hwnd=%p subsurface=%d,%d+%dx%d\n", surface->hwnd, x, y, width, height);
 
